      <title>Re: How will we know when an unlocking mechanism is triggered?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=17757#M17757</link>
      <description>No, y'all are misunderstanding me. I'm not asking how we'll know &lt;i&gt;when&lt;/i&gt; the triggers have been completed; I'm asking how we'll know &lt;i&gt;what &lt;/i&gt;those&#xD;
triggers were. For instance, let's say Nagafen, Vox and Innoruuk have&#xD;
all been killed, and Kunark still isn't open. Then some guild clears&#xD;
Fear, killing Cazic Thule himself in the process, and suddenly Kunark&#xD;
is open. Well great! I guess then we'll know that Fear was part of the&#xD;
unlocking mechanism, but were Vox and Nagafen? Was Hate? Or was the&#xD;
whole bloody thing just about clearing Fear? For that matter, could a&#xD;
dozen other things have been part of it and no one knew it? Was it&#xD;
enough to kill Inny, or did the Maestro have to die too? Were there&#xD;
non-raid components that were completed along the way by random people&#xD;
on-server? &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
My point is that without some sort of message as each part of the&#xD;
unlocking mechanism is completed, we could end up unlocking the next&#xD;
expansion without really knowing how the heck we did it.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
